parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition module can cause the engine to stall or cut off while driving, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, making it difficult to control the vehicle and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or cuts off while driving
the vehicle is difficult to control
the power steering and brakes are affected
the vehicle will not restart
and the ignition module needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to flickering lights, smoke, and even fires under the hood, which can spread and cause damage to the vehicle and potentially injure occupants.
symptoms: The lights flicker
smoke appears under the hood
flames are visible under the hood
the alternator needs to be replaced
and the vehicle may not turn off even when the key is removed from the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical wiring issues can cause fires, especially in the rear of the vehicle, which can spread and cause damage to the vehicle and potentially injure occupants.
symptoms: The wiring catches fire
especially in the rear of the vehicle
the left rear tail light is affected
and the vehicle is at risk of further electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tread Separation and Air Loss in Firestone FR480 Tires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tread separation and air loss in Firestone FR480 tires can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden shaking or vibration while driving
feeling a bump under the vehicle
tire blowout
loss of air pressure
tire tread separation.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tread Separation in Triumph Radio 2000 Tires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tread separation in Triumph Radio 2000 tires can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities, as well as damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Sudden shaking or vibration while driving
feeling a bump under the vehicle
tire blowout
loss of air pressure
tire tread separation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty gas cap venting can cause the fuel tank to pressurize, leading to gas leaks and potentially creating a fire hazard.
symptoms: Gas leaks from the gas cap
especially on hot days
gas cap hisses or makes a loud noise when opened
gas sprays out of the cap when opened
fuel tank pressurizes.
